1
00:00:02,500 --> 00:00:06,220
Everyone would like some sort 
of like a Hollywood epiphany:

2
00:00:06,430 --> 00:00:08,560
like the twig breaks, then
[snaps fingers]

3
00:00:08,560 --> 00:00:10,140
you become enlightened.

4
00:00:10,140 --> 00:00:13,800
[Hollywood Epiphany vs. Inner Awakening]

5
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:17,390
But our concept 
even of enlightenment is

6
00:00:17,390 --> 00:00:21,810
it’s not a static state,
it’s not stagnant.

7
00:00:21,900 --> 00:00:26,800
So we are capable of growing.

8
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:29,800
If the finite is going to meet 
the Infinite,

9
00:00:29,800 --> 00:00:32,800
come in connection
with the Infinite,

10
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:36,300
at what point 
is it stagnant?

11
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:46,570
At what point does the finite imbibe
or contain the whole of the Infinite?

12
00:00:47,700 --> 00:00:50,610
That’s not tenable.

13
00:00:50,610 --> 00:00:54,750
But as much as of what
Kṛṣṇa wants to reveal to us—

14
00:00:54,750 --> 00:00:56,800
that much we will know

15
00:00:56,800 --> 00:01:03,260
about ourselves, about Him,
about the Supreme Reality.

16
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:06,200
Our strategy,
the devotional strategy

17
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:09,300
is to take shelter 
of a superior devotee

18
00:01:09,300 --> 00:01:12,300
through association
and service.

19
00:01:12,300 --> 00:01:14,690
And that’s considered
a safe position.

20
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:18,370
But you heard recently 
I used this expression

21
00:01:18,370 --> 00:01:23,280
quoting Śrīla Guru Maharāj
about the inner awakenment

22
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:24,720
of a disciple.

23
00:01:24,720 --> 00:01:27,180
So according 
to inner awakenment,

24
00:01:27,180 --> 00:01:33,010
not only how we conceive guru—
how we conceive our self,

25
00:01:33,010 --> 00:01:36,070
our notion of self, 
our conception of self.

26
00:01:36,090 --> 00:01:40,810
But that’s going to require
the dissolution of the layers covering

27
00:01:40,810 --> 00:01:46,210
to allow the actual form
to manifest.

28
00:01:46,900 --> 00:01:50,780
Śrīla Guru Maharāj has also given 
an interesting example in this regard

29
00:01:50,780 --> 00:01:54,890
about sandalwood
and sandalwood pulp.

30
00:01:54,890 --> 00:01:57,100
You know sandalwood?

31
00:01:57,100 --> 00:02:00,470
It’s a type of wood,
fragrant wood,

32
00:02:00,470 --> 00:02:02,340
like, you’ve heard 
of sandalwood oil,

33
00:02:02,340 --> 00:02:04,600
well, it comes from 
the sandalwood tree.

34
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:09,830
So, and … do we have it here?
We have it here.

35
00:02:10,300 --> 00:02:13,190
So, sandalwood …

36
00:02:13,190 --> 00:02:16,190
The sevak or the archak

37
00:02:16,190 --> 00:02:19,130
who’s doing 
the service to the Deity,

38
00:02:19,130 --> 00:02:22,370
they take a stone, pour
some rose water on the stone,

39
00:02:22,370 --> 00:02:26,500
then they take a bar
of sandalwood

40
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:30,800
and start rubbing that
against the grinding stone.

41
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:34,300
And what happens is
the sandalwood stick

42
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:38,670
is transformed 
into its essence,

43
00:02:38,670 --> 00:02:40,710
and that fragrance,
sandalwood fragrance

44
00:02:40,710 --> 00:02:43,700
comes out,
and it’s in this paste form.

45
00:02:43,700 --> 00:02:45,700
But what you’ll see,
happens in time:

46
00:02:45,700 --> 00:02:48,510
say, the sandalwood stick 
is like this—

47
00:02:48,970 --> 00:02:51,400
it starts diminishing.

48
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:56,200
So, the more it’s turning 
into its essential fragrance,

49
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:59,200
it’s dissipating.

50
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:03,700
So through apparent
self-dissipation,

51
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:06,900
by engaging ourselves in service,
putting all of our …

52
00:03:06,900 --> 00:03:09,750
what’s available
to us at present,

53
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:13,800
what we’ve acquired,
our acquired energy—

54
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:16,600
by dedicating that in service

55
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:23,040
that external conception of self
starts dissipating,

56
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:28,150
and the outcome 
is the essence,

57
00:03:28,150 --> 00:03:31,463
the real self, 
the servitor self—

58
00:03:31,463 --> 00:03:32,533
svarup.

